{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775903966790,"sessionID":"ses_283e038e3ffe4kJ5JqHYQRhKXf","part":{"id":"prt_d7c200179001DIIsi01GuR3pL5","messageID":"msg_d7c1fe2a8001z6UxfMbBeylo0L","sessionID":"ses_283e038e3ffe4kJ5JqHYQRhKXf","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-faf5edc48d8248c9a81c798e9e51ad61","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: E2E Integration Tests for client-go\n2: \n3: **AR:** AR-041 — E2E 集成测试  \n4: **Module:** test/e2e  \n5: **Language:** Go  \n6: **Size:** L\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## OpenSpec Format\n11: \n12: Each requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## REQ-001: Clientset Construction and Interface Compliance\n17: \n18: ### Description\n19: \n20: Clientset must be constructable from REST config and implement the Interface correctly.\n21: \n22: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n23: \n24: #### Scenario: Create Clientset from REST config\n25: - **GIVEN** a valid Kubernetes REST config with cluster endpoint and credentials\n26: - **WHEN** `NewForConfig` is called with the config\n27: - **THEN** a non-nil `*Clientset` is returned with no error\n28: - **AND** the clientset implements the `Interface` interface\n29: - **AND** `RuntimeV1alpha1()` returns a valid `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Create Clientset with custom HTTP client\n32: - **GIVEN** a valid REST config and a custom `*http.Client` with custom timeouts\n33: - **WHEN** `NewForConfigAndClient` is called\n34: - **THEN** the returned `*Clientset` uses the provided HTTP client\n35: - **AND** all API calls use the custom client configuration\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Clientset Discovery interface works\n38: - **GIVEN** a Clientset connected to a running Kubernetes cluster\n39: - **WHEN** `Discovery()` is called\n40: - **THEN** the returned `DiscoveryInterface` can list API groups\n41: - **AND** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` is discoverable\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Panics on invalid config with NewForConfigOrDie\n44: - **GIVEN** an invalid REST config (nil or missing required fields)\n45: - **WHEN** `NewForConfigOrDie` is called\n46: - **THEN** the function panics\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## REQ-002: AgentRuntime CRUD Operations\n51: \n52: ### Description\n53: \n54: AgentRuntimeInterface must support full CRUD lifecycle against a live cluster.\n55: \n56: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n57: \n58: #### Scenario: Create an AgentRuntime resource\n59: - **GIVEN** a Clientset connected to a Kubernetes cluster with CRDs installed\n60: - **AND** a valid `AgentRuntime` spec in namespace `test-ns`\n61: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})` is called\n62: - **THEN** the returned `AgentRuntime` has the correct name and namespace\n63: - **AND** the resource exists in the cluster with `kubectl get agentruntime`\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Get an existing AgentRuntime\n66: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-agent` exists in namespace `test-ns`\n67: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Get(ctx, \"test-agent\", metav1.GetOptions{})` is called\n68: - **THEN** the returned `AgentRuntime` has name `test-agent`\n69: - **AND** the spec matches the created resource\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: List AgentRuntimes in namespace\n72: - **GIVEN** three AgentRuntimes exist in namespace `test-ns`\n73: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})` is called\n74: - **THEN** the returned `AgentRuntimeList` contains exactly 3 items\n75: - **AND** all items have namespace `test-ns`\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: List AgentRuntimes with label selector\n78: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes exist with labels `app=test` and `app=prod`\n79: - **WHEN** `List` is called with `ListOptions{LabelSelector: \"app=test\"}`\n80: - **THEN** only AgentRuntimes with `app=test` label are returned\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: Update an AgentRuntime\n83: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-agent` exists with `spec.replicas=1`\n84: - **WHEN** the spec is updated to `replicas=3` and `Update` is called\n85: - **THEN** the returned AgentRuntime has `spec.replicas=3`\n86: - **AND** the resource in cluster reflects the update\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: UpdateStatus subresource\n89: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with empty status\n90: - **WHEN** `UpdateStatus` is called with status conditions set\n91: - **THEN** only the status subresource is updated\n92: - **AND** the spec remains unchanged\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Delete an AgentRuntime\n95: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `test-agent` exists\n96: - **WHEN** `Delete(ctx, \"test-agent\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})` is called\n97: - **THEN** the error is nil\n98: - **AND** subsequent `Get` returns a `NotFound` error\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: DeleteCollection with selector\n101: - **GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntimes exist with label `cleanup=true`\n102: - **WHEN** `DeleteCollection` is called with matching label selector\n103: - **THEN** all matching resources are deleted\n104: - **AND** non-matching resources remain\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Patch an AgentRuntime\n107: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `spec.replicas=1`\n108: - **WHEN** `Patch` is called with `MergePatchType` and JSON patch data `{\"spec\":{\"replicas\":5}}`\n109: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime is updated with `spec.replicas=5`\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Watch AgentRuntime changes\n112: - **GIVEN** a Watch is started with `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`\n113: - **WHEN** an AgentRuntime is created, updated, and deleted\n114: - **THEN** the watch channel receives `ADDED`, `MODIFIED`, and `DELETED` events respectively\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ## REQ-003: CodeInterpreter CRUD Operations\n119: \n120: ### Description\n121: \n122: CodeInterpreterInterface must support full CRUD lifecycle against a live cluster.\n123: \n124: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: Create a CodeInterpreter resource\n127: - **GIVEN** a Clientset and valid `CodeInterpreter` spec\n128: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreters(\"test-ns\").Create(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.CreateOptions{})` is called\n129: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter is created in the cluster\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Full CRUD cycle for CodeInterpreter\n132: - **GIVEN** a clean namespace\n133: - **WHEN** Create, Get, Update, UpdateStatus, List, and Delete operations are performed\n134: - **THEN** all operations complete successfully\n135: - **AND** the final state matches expectations\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: Watch CodeInterpreter events\n138: - **GIVEN** a Watch is started for CodeInterpreters\n139: - **WHEN** multiple CodeInterpreters are created concurrently\n140: - **THEN** all `ADDED` events are received on the watch channel\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter List across namespaces\n143: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreters exist in namespaces `ns-a` and `ns-b`\n144: - **WHEN** `List` is called in each namespace\n145: - **THEN** correct resources are returned per namespace\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## REQ-004: SharedInformerFactory Operations\n150: \n151: ### Description\n152: \n153: SharedInformerFactory must correctly start, sync, and shutdown informers.\n154: \n155: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Start and Shutdown informer factory\n158: - **GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` with a Clientset\n159: - **WHEN** `Start(stopCh)` is called\n160: - **THEN** informers begin syncing\n161: - **AND** calling `Shutdown()` stops all informers gracefully\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: WaitForCacheSync reports sync status\n164: - **GIVEN** a SharedInformerFactory with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers\n165: - **WHEN** `WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)` is called\n166: - **THEN** the returned map contains `true` for both types\n167: - **AND** all caches are synced with the cluster\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime informer and lister work together\n170: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime informer started and synced\n171: - **AND** an AgentRuntime `test-ar` exists in `test-ns`\n172: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes().Lister().AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Get(\"test-ar\")` is called\n173: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime is returned from cache (no API call)\n174: - **AND** the object matches the cluster state\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter informer and lister work together\n177: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter informer started and synced\n178: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreters().Lister().List(labels.Everything())` is called\n179: - **THEN** all CodeInterpreters across namespaces are returned from cache\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Namespace-scoped informer factory\n182: - **GIVEN** `NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` with `WithNamespace(\"limited-ns\")`\n183: - **WHEN** informers are started\n184: - **THEN** only resources in `limited-ns` are cached\n185: - **AND** resources in other namespaces are not visible to the lister\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Custom resync period\n188: - **GIVEN** a factory created with `defaultResync=30*time.Second`\n189: - **WHEN** informers run for longer than resync period\n190: - **THEN** full resync events are triggered periodically\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: ForResource returns correct informer\n193: - **GIVEN** a SharedInformerFactory\n194: - **WHEN** `ForResource(v1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithResource(\"agentruntimes\"))` is called\n195: - **THEN** a GenericInformer for AgentRuntimes is returned\n196: - **AND** the informer is the same instance as from `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()`\n197: \n198: #### Scenario: TweakListOptions filters list calls\n199: - **GIVEN** a factory with `WithTweakListOptions` that sets `LabelSelector`\n200: - **WHEN** the informer performs list operations\n201: - **THEN** only resources matching the selector are cached\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## REQ-005: Lister Operations\n206: \n207: ### Description\n208: \n209: Listers must provide efficient cached access to resources.\n210: \n211: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeLister lists across namespaces\n214: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes in namespaces `ns-a` and `ns-b`\n215: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimeLister.List(labels.Everything())` is called\n216: - **THEN** all AgentRuntimes from both namespaces are returned\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister filters by namespace\n219: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes in namespaces `ns-a` and `ns-b`\n220: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"ns-a\").List(labels.Everything())` is called\n221: - **THEN** only AgentRuntimes in `ns-a` are returned\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Lister returns error for non-existent resource\n224: - **GIVEN** no AgentRuntime named `nonexistent` in namespace `test-ns`\n225: - **WHEN** `AgentRuntimes(\"test-ns\").Get(\"nonexistent\")` is called\n226: - **THEN** an error is returned (not nil)\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreterLister mirrors AgentRuntimeLister behavior\n229: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreters in multiple namespaces\n230: - **WHEN** both `List` and `Get` operations are performed\n231: - **THEN** behavior matches AgentRuntimeLister patterns\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Lister List with label selector\n234: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes with various labels\n235: - **WHEN** `List` is called with a label selector\n236: - **THEN** only matching resources are returned\n237: \n238: ---\n239: \n240: ## REQ-006: Fake Clientset for Unit Testing\n241: \n242: ### Description\n243: \n244: Fake clientset must track objects and support testing patterns.\n245: \n246: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: Fake clientset tracks objects\n249: - **GIVEN** `NewSimpleClientset()` creates an empty fake clientset\n250: - **WHEN** AgentRuntimes are created via the fake client\n251: - **THEN** `List` returns all created objects\n252: - **AND** no actual API calls are made\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Fake clientset returns injected errors\n255: - **GIVEN** a fake clientset with a reactor that returns errors\n256: - **WHEN** Create/Update/Delete operations are called\n257: - **THEN** the injected error is returned\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: Fake clientset supports Watch\n260: - **GIVEN** a fake clientset with an AgentRuntime\n261: - **WHEN** `Watch` is called and the object is modified via the fake client\n262: - **THEN** watch events are generated and sent to the watcher\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Fake clientset AddReactor captures actions\n265: - **GIVEN** a fake clientset with an AddReactor for \"create\"\n266: - **WHEN** Create is called\n267: - **THEN** the reactor captures the action\n268: - **AND** custom behavior can be implemented\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ## REQ-007: Error Handling and Edge Cases\n273: \n274: ### Description\n275: \n276: Client must handle Kubernetes API errors correctly.\n277: \n278: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Context cancellation aborts operations\n281: - **GIVEN** a context that is cancelled before API call completes\n282: - **WHEN** any CRUD operation is called with the cancelled context\n283: - **THEN** the operation returns a context cancellation error\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: NotFound error for missing resource\n286: - **GIVEN** no resource named `missing` exists\n287: - **WHEN** `Get(ctx, \"missing\", metav1.GetOptions{})` is called\n288: - **THEN** a `*errors.StatusError` with status code 404 is returned\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: AlreadyExists error on duplicate create\n291: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime `duplicate` already exists\n292: - **WHEN** `Create` is called with the same name\n293: - **THEN** an `AlreadyExists` error is returned\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: Invalid field errors are structured\n296: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with an invalid spec field\n297: - **WHEN** `Create` is called\n298: - **THEN** the error can be cast to `*errors.StatusError`\n299: - **AND** `Status().Details.Causes` contains field-level error details\n300: \n301: #### Scenario: Timeout error on slow API\n302: - **GIVEN** a context with short deadline\n303: - **AND** API server is slow\n304: - **WHEN** operation is called\n305: - **THEN** timeout error is returned\n306: \n307: ---\n308: \n309: ## REQ-008: Concurrent Operations\n310: \n311: ### Description\n312: \n313: Client must handle concurrent operations safely.\n314: \n315: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n316: \n317: #### Scenario: Concurrent creates succeed with unique names\n318: - **GIVEN** a Clientset and 10 goroutines each creating an AgentRuntime\n319: - **AND** each goroutine uses a unique name\n320: - **WHEN** all goroutines complete\n321: - **THEN** all 10 AgentRuntimes exist in the cluster\n322: \n323: #### Scenario: Concurrent reads from informer cache\n324: - **GIVEN** an informer with synced cache\n325: - **WHEN** 100 concurrent `Lister.Get` calls are made\n326: - **THEN** all calls complete without race conditions\n327: - **AND** data remains consistent\n328: \n329: #### Scenario: Watch handles high event throughput\n330: - **GIVEN** a Watch started on AgentRuntimes\n331: - **WHEN** 100 AgentRuntimes are created rapidly\n332: - **THEN** all 100 `ADDED` events are received\n333: - **AND** no events are dropped\n334: \n335: #### Scenario: Concurrent updates with conflict resolution\n336: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with multiple concurrent updates\n337: - **WHEN** some updates conflict due to resource version\n338: - **THEN** conflict errors are returned for stale updates\n339: - **AND** retry succeeds with fresh resource version\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ## REQ-009: Resource Version and Optimistic Concurrency\n344: \n345: ### Description\n346: \n347: Client must support Kubernetes optimistic concurrency control.\n348: \n349: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n350: \n351: #### Scenario: Update fails with stale resource version\n352: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `resourceVersion=v1`\n353: - **AND** the resource was updated by another client (now `v2`)\n354: - **WHEN** an Update is attempted with `resourceVersion=v1`\n355: - **THEN** a conflict error is returned\n356: - **AND** the error status code is 409\n357: \n358: #### Scenario: Get with ResourceVersion returns consistent snapshot\n359: - **GIVEN** a valid `resourceVersion` from a previous list\n360: - **WHEN** `Get` is called with `metav1.GetOptions{ResourceVersion: rv}`\n361: - **THEN** the data is consistent with that resource version\n362: \n363: #### Scenario: List with ResourceVersion\n364: - **GIVEN** a resourceVersion from a previous list\n365: - **WHEN** `List` is called with that ResourceVersion\n366: - **THEN** response includes matching ResourceVersion\n367: - **AND** data is consistent with requested version\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## REQ-010: Integration with Kubernetes Ecosystem\n372: \n373: ### Description\n374: \n375: client-go must integrate with common Kubernetes patterns and tools.\n376: \n377: ### Acceptance Scenarios\n378: \n379: #### Scenario: Works with controller-runtime\n380: - **GIVEN** a controller-runtime Manager\n381: - **WHEN** the client-go Clientset is used alongside controller-runtime\n382: - **THEN** both clients can operate on the same AgentRuntime resources\n383: - **AND** no conflicts occur\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: Informer integrates with workqueue\n386: - **GIVEN** an informer and a `workqueue.TypedRateLimitingInterface`\n387: - **WHEN** an Add/Update/Delete handler enqueues the key\n388: - **THEN** the workqueue processes keys in order with rate limiting\n389: \n390: #### Scenario: Metrics endpoint exposes informer stats\n391: - **GIVEN** a metrics registry and an informer factory\n392: - **WHEN** informer metrics are registered\n393: - **THEN** cache hits, misses, and sync duration are exposed as metrics\n394: \n395: #### Scenario: Leader election with informer factory\n396: - **GIVEN** a leader election lock\n397: - **WHEN** leader is elected\n398: - **THEN** informer factory starts\n399: - **AND** when leader lost, factory shuts down\n400: \n401: ---\n402: \n403: ## Summary\n404: \n405: | REQ ID | Component | Test Count |\n406: |--------|-----------|------------|\n407: | REQ-001 | Clientset Construction | 4 |\n408: | REQ-002 | AgentRuntime CRUD | 10 |\n409: | REQ-003 | CodeInterpreter CRUD | 4 |\n410: | REQ-004 | SharedInformerFactory | 8 |\n411: | REQ-005 | Lister Operations | 5 |\n412: | REQ-006 | Fake Clientset | 4 |\n413: | REQ-007 | Error Handling | 5 |\n414: | REQ-008 | Concurrent Operations | 4 |\n415: | REQ-009 | Resource Version | 3 |\n416: | REQ-010 | Ecosystem Integration | 4 |\n417: \n418: **Total Scenarios:** 51\n419: \n420: ---\n421: \n422: ## Test Infrastructure\n423: \n424: ### E2E Test Setup\n425: \n426: ```go\n427: // test/e2e/e2e_test.go\n428: package e2e\n429: \n430: import (\n431:     \"testing\"\n432:     \"time\"\n433:     \n434:     runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n435:     clientset \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n436:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions\"\n437:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n438:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n439: )\n440: \n441: func newTestClientset(t *testing.T) clientset.Interface {\n442:     loadingRules := clientcmd.NewDefaultClientConfigLoadingRules()\n443:     configOverrides := &clientcmd.ConfigOverrides{}\n444:     config, err := clientcmd.NewNonInteractiveDeferredLoadingClientConfig(\n445:         loadingRules, configOverrides).ClientConfig()\n446:     if err != nil {\n447:         t.Fatalf(\"Failed to load kubeconfig: %v\", err)\n448:     }\n449:     cs, err := clientset.NewForConfig(config)\n450:     if err != nil {\n451:         t.Fatalf(\"Failed to create clientset: %v\", err)\n452:     }\n453:     return cs\n454: }\n455: \n456: func newTestAgentRuntime(name, namespace string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime {\n457:     return &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n458:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n459:             Name:      name,\n460:             Namespace: namespace,\n461:         },\n462:     }\n463: }\n464: \n465: func newTestCodeInterpreter(name, namespace string) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter {\n466:     return &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n467:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n468:             Name:      name,\n469:             Namespace: namespace,\n470:         },\n471:     }\n472: }\n473: ```\n474: \n475: ### Test Tags\n476: \n477: ```go\n478: // +build e2e\n479: // Run: go test -tags=e2e ./test/e2e/...\n480: ```\n481: \n482: ---\n483: \n484: ## Dependencies\n485: \n486: | Dependency | Purpose |\n487: |------------|---------|\n488: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Kubernetes client library |\n489: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | API machinery |\n490: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated client |\n491: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Controller patterns (optional) |\n492: \n493: ---\n494: \n495: ## Validation Checklist\n496: \n497: - [ ] Clientset construction from REST config\n498: - [ ] AgentRuntime CRUD operations against live cluster\n499: - [ ] CodeInterpreter CRUD operations against live cluster\n500: - [ ] SharedInformerFactory Start/Shutdown/WaitForCacheSync\n501: - [ ] Informer integration with Listers\n502: - [ ] Namespace-scoped informer filtering\n503: - [ ] Lister Get/List operations\n504: - [ ] Fake clientset object tracking\n505: - [ ] Error handling (NotFound, AlreadyExists, Conflict)\n506: - [ ] Context cancellation handling\n507: - [ ] Concurrent operations safety\n508: - [ ] Watch event reception\n509: - [ ] Resource version conflict detection\n510: - [ ] Integration with controller-runtime\n511: - [ ] Integration with workqueue patterns\n\n(End of file - total 511 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: E2E Integration Tests for client-go\n\n**AR:** AR-041 — E2E 集成测试  \n**Module:** test/e2e  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## OpenSpec Format\n\nEach requirement follows GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure for acceptance scenarios.\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Clientset Construction and Interface Compliance\n\n### Description\n\nClientset must be constructable from REST config and implement the Interface correctly.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775903966731,"end":1775903966788}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775903966796,"sessionID":"ses_283e038e3ffe4kJ5JqHYQRhKXf","part":{"id":"prt_d7c1ff90c001lg5Tk6l0YZJdKa","messageID":"msg_d7c1fe2a8001z6UxfMbBeylo0L","sessionID":"ses_283e038e3ffe4kJ5JqHYQRhKXf","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-854c1ff2d6284b9a978d2d42a9198772","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-041/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-041/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-041 — E2E 集成测试\n2: \n3: **Module:** test/e2e  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: [TO BE FILLED: Add overview for E2E 集成测试]\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: [TO BE FILLED: Add GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios]\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## Constants Summary\n22: \n23: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n24: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n25: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Dependencies Summary\n30: \n31: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n32: |---------|---------|---------|\n33: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## File Changes Summary\n38: \n39: | File | Action | Description |\n40: |------|--------|-------------|\n41: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## References\n46: \n47: - [TO BE FILLED: Add relevant references]\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## Validation Checklist\n52: \n53: - [ ] [TO BE FILLED]\n\n(End of file - total 53 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-041 — E2E 集成测试\n\n**Module:** test/e2e  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Add overview for E2E 集成测试]\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n[T