{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775904089613,"sessionID":"ses_283e038e3ffe4kJ5JqHYQRhKXf","part":{"id":"prt_d7c21e5a5001lkvocDtNGRZY7N","messageID":"msg_d7c207615001iHA2rB7F6XMFoi","sessionID":"ses_283e038e3ffe4kJ5JqHYQRhKXf","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-0aaee7d73e73460ba86957a224024032","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-042/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-042 — Docusaurus 文档站框架\n\n**Module:** docs  \n**Language:** TypeScript  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nInitialize a Docusaurus 3.x documentation site for AgentCube, consolidating scattered design documents, specifications, and API references into a structured, searchable platform. The site provides unified navigation for architecture guides, API documentation, deployment manuals, and quick-start tutorials.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Docusaurus project initialization\n\nThe system SHALL initialize a Docusaurus 3.x project with TypeScript configuration, classic preset, and standard directory structure.\n\n#### Scenario: Project scaffold created\n\n- **GIVEN** the repository root directory exists\n- **WHEN** Docusaurus initialization is executed with TypeScript template\n- **THEN** the `docs/` directory SHALL contain `docusaurus.config.ts`, `sidebars.ts`, `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, and `src/pages/index.tsx`\n- **AND** the project SHALL use `@docusaurus/preset-classic` as the default preset\n\n#### Scenario: TypeScript configuration valid\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/tsconfig.json` exists\n- **WHEN** TypeScript compiler runs on the project\n- **THEN** no compilation errors SHALL occur\n- **AND** strict mode SHALL be enabled for type safety\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Site configuration structure\n\nThe system SHALL provide a valid `docusaurus.config.ts` declaring site metadata, navigation, plugins, and theme settings.\n\n#### Scenario: Required config fields present\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` is parsed\n- **WHEN** the configuration is validated\n- **THEN** the config SHALL include `title`, `tagline`, `url`, `baseUrl`, `favicon`, `organizationName`, `projectName`, `themeConfig` with `navbar` and `footer`, and `presets` array\n- **AND** the `url` SHALL match the production deployment target\n\n#### Scenario: Navbar items configured\n\n- **GIVEN** `themeConfig.navbar.items` is defined\n- **WHEN** the site renders the navigation bar\n- **THEN** the navbar SHALL include links to Documentation, API Reference, Architecture, Deployment, and Getting Started\n- **AND** each item SHALL have a `to` or `href` property pointing to valid routes\n\n#### Scenario: Footer links configured\n\n- **GIVEN** `themeConfig.footer.links` is defined\n- **WHEN** the site renders the footer\n- **THEN** the footer SHALL include sections for Documentation, Community, and More\n- **AND** each link SHALL have valid `label` and `to` or `href` properties\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Sidebar structure definition\n\nThe system SHALL define a `sidebars.ts` file organizing documentation into hierarchical categories.\n\n#### Scenario: Sidebar categories defined\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/sidebars.ts` is imported by the config\n- **WHEN** the site generates the sidebar navigation\n- **THEN** the sidebar SHALL include categories: `gettingStarted`, `architecture`, `api`, `deployment`, `changelog`\n- **AND** each category SHALL have a `label` and `items` array with document IDs\n\n#### Scenario: Sidebar items resolve to documents\n\n- **GIVEN** a sidebar item references document ID `getting-started/installation`\n- **WHEN** the user navigates to that sidebar entry\n- **THEN** the corresponding `docs/docs/getting-started/installation.md` SHALL be rendered\n- **AND** navigation SHALL work without broken links\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Architecture documentation pages\n\nThe system SHALL integrate existing design documents into structured architecture pages under `docs/docs/architecture/`.\n\n#### Scenario: Architecture overview page exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/docs/architecture/overview.md` is created\n- **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/architecture/overview`\n- **THEN** the page SHALL contain content derived from the repository's `design.md`\n- **AND** the page SHALL include system architecture diagrams using Mermaid syntax\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox orchestration page exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/docs/architecture/sandbox.md` is created\n- **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/architecture/sandbox`\n- **THEN** the page SHALL contain content derived from `sandbox-orchestration/design.md`\n- **AND** the page SHALL explain sandbox lifecycle, session routing, and cleanup mechanisms\n\n#### Scenario: Architecture pages linked in sidebar\n\n- **GIVEN** the sidebar `architecture` category\n- **WHEN** the category is expanded\n- **THEN** items SHALL include `overview`, `sandbox`, `session-routing`, and `idle-cleanup`\n- **AND** each item SHALL correspond to a valid markdown file\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: API reference pages\n\nThe system SHALL provide API documentation pages for Python SDK and Go client-go library.\n\n#### Scenario: Python SDK API page exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/docs/api/sdk-python/client.md` is created\n- **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/api/sdk-python/client`\n- **THEN** the page SHALL document `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient`, session management methods, and exception classes\n- **AND** the page SHALL include code examples for common usage patterns\n\n#### Scenario: Client-go API page exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/docs/api/client-go/overview.md` is created\n- **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/api/client-go/overview`\n- **THEN** the page SHALL document Clientset construction, CRUD interfaces, informer factory usage, and lister patterns\n- **AND** the page SHALL include Go code examples matching the `client-go/` implementation\n\n#### Scenario: API sidebar category structured\n\n- **GIVEN** the sidebar `api` category\n- **WHEN** the category is expanded\n- **THEN** items SHALL be organized under subcategories `sdk-python` and `client-go`\n- **AND** each subcategory SHALL list relevant API reference documents\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Deployment guide pages\n\nThe system SHALL provide deployment documentation pages covering Kubernetes configuration and Helm charts.\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes deployment page exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/docs/deployment/kubernetes.md` is created\n- **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/deployment/kubernetes`\n- **THEN** the page SHALL contain content derived from `deployment/design.md`\n- **AND** the page SHALL document CRD installation, namespace setup, resource requirements, and Helm values\n\n#### Scenario: Helm chart parameters documented\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/docs/deployment/helm-chart.md` is created\n- **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/deployment/helm-chart`\n- **THEN** the page SHALL document all configurable Helm values from `manifests/` charts\n- **AND** the page SHALL provide default values and recommended configurations\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Getting started tutorials\n\nThe system SHALL provide quick-start documentation pages for new users.\n\n#### Scenario: Installation page exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/docs/getting-started/installation.md` is created\n- **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/getting-started/installation`\n- **THEN** the page SHALL document prerequisites (Go 1.24, Python 3.10+, Kubernetes cluster)\n- **AND** the page SHALL provide CLI installation commands and SDK pip install instructions\n\n#### Scenario: First sandbox tutorial exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/docs/getting-started/first-sandbox.md` is created\n- **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/getting-started/first-sandbox`\n- **THEN** the page SHALL provide a step-by-step guide to create a sandbox, execute code, and retrieve results\n- **AND** the page SHALL include working code samples for both Python SDK and CLI\n\n#### Scenario: Getting started sidebar sequence\n\n- **GIVEN** the sidebar `gettingStarted` category\n- **WHEN** the category is expanded\n- **THEN** items SHALL be ordered: `installation`, `first-sandbox`, `configuration`, `next-steps`\n- **AND** the sequence SHALL follow a logical learning path\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Version and changelog pages\n\nThe system SHALL provide changelog documentation integrated with GitHub Releases.\n\n#### Scenario: Changelog index page exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/docs/changelog/index.md` is created\n- **WHEN** the user accesses `/docs/changelog`\n- **THEN** the page SHALL list version releases in reverse chronological order\n- **AND** each release entry SHALL link to detailed changelog or GitHub Release\n\n#### Scenario: Changelog sidebar configured\n\n- **GIVEN** the sidebar `changelog` category\n- **WHEN** the category is rendered\n- **THEN** it SHALL link to `index` and individual version documents\n- **AND** documents SHALL use frontmatter `id` matching their version\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Search functionality integration\n\nThe system SHALL integrate search capability using Algolia DocSearch or local search plugin.\n\n#### Scenario: Algolia DocSearch configured\n\n- **GIVEN** Algolia credentials are provided in environment\n- **WHEN** `themeConfig.algolia` is configured in `docusaurus.config.ts`\n- **THEN** the search bar SHALL appear in the navbar\n- **AND** search queries SHALL return indexed documentation pages\n\n#### Scenario: Local search fallback\n\n- **GIVEN** Algolia credentials are not available\n- **WHEN** `@docusaurus/plugin-search-local` is included in plugins\n- **THEN** the search bar SHALL work with locally indexed content\n- **AND** search results SHALL be generated at build time\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Multi-language support configuration\n\nThe system SHALL configure i18n structure supporting English and Chinese language variants.\n\n#### Scenario: i18n directories initialized\n\n- **GIVEN** i18n configuration in `docusaurus.config.ts`\n- **WHEN** the site is built\n- **THEN** `docs/i18n/zh-Hans/` directory SHALL exist for Chinese translations\n- **AND** `docs/i18n/en/` SHALL contain default English content\n\n#### Scenario: Language switcher in navbar\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple locales are configured\n- **WHEN** the navbar renders\n- **THEN** a language dropdown SHALL appear allowing locale switching\n- **AND** switching SHALL preserve the current page path in the target locale\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CI/CD integration for documentation\n\nThe system SHALL provide GitHub Actions workflow for automatic documentation build and deployment.\n\n#### Scenario: Docs workflow file exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `.github/workflows/docs.yml` is created\n- **WHEN** changes are pushed to `docs/` directory or `main` branch\n- **THEN** the workflow SHALL trigger on `push` paths matching `docs/**`\n- **AND** the workflow SHALL use Node.js 18.x and run `npm install && npm run build`\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment to GitHub Pages\n\n- **GIVEN** the docs workflow completes successfully\n- **WHEN** the build job produces the `build/` output\n- **THEN** the deploy job SHALL publish to `gh-pages` branch\n- **AND** the site SHALL be accessible at the configured GitHub Pages URL\n\n#### Scenario: Build failure notification\n\n- **GIVEN** the docs build fails due to syntax error\n- **WHEN** the workflow runs\n- **THEN** the job SHALL fail with error details\n- **AND** subsequent deployment SHALL be skipped\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Homepage and custom styling\n\nThe system SHALL provide a custom homepage and styling reflecting AgentCube branding.\n\n#### Scenario: Homepage renders correctly\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/src/pages/index.tsx` exists\n- **WHEN** the user accesses the root URL\n- **THEN** the homepage SHALL display hero section with project title and tagline\n- **AND** the homepage SHALL include call-to-action buttons linking to Getting Started and Documentation\n\n#### Scenario: Custom CSS applied\n\n- **GIVEN** `docs/src/css/custom.css` exists\n- **WHEN** the site renders\n- **THEN** the styles SHALL override Docusaurus defaults for colors, fonts, and spacing\n- **AND** the theme SHALL match AgentCube project branding guidelines\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Makefile integration\n\nThe system SHALL provide Makefile targets for local documentation development.\n\n#### Scenario: Docs build target exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` is updated with docs targets\n- **WHEN** `make docs` is executed\n- **THEN** the command SHALL run `cd docs && npm run build`\n- **AND** the output SHALL be in `docs/build/` directory\n\n#### Scenario: Docs start target exists\n\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` is updated with docs targets\n- **WHEN** `make docs-start` is executed\n- **THEN** the command SHALL run `cd docs && npm run start`\n- **AND** the local development server SHALL start on port 3000\n\n---\n\n## Constants Summary\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| `DOCUSAURUS_VERSION` | `3.x` | `package.json` | Docusaurus framework version |\n| `NODE_VERSION` | `18.x` | `.github/workflows/docs.yml` | Node.js runtime for CI |\n| `DEFAULT_PORT` | `3000` | `docusaurus.config.ts` | Local development server port |\n| `BASE_URL` | `/agentcube/` | `docusaurus.config.ts` | Production base path |\n| `SITE_URL` | `https://volcano-sh.github.io` | `docusaurus.config.ts` | Production deployment URL |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies Summary\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `@docusaurus/core` | `3.x` | Docusaurus core framework |\n| `@docusaurus/preset-classic` | `3.x` | Classic preset with blog, docs, pages |\n| `@docusaurus/theme-search-algolia` | `3.x` | Algolia search integration |\n| `@docusaurus/plugin-search-local` | `latest` | Local search fallback plugin |\n| `@docusaurus/module-type-aliases` | `3.x` | TypeScript type definitions |\n| `react` | `18.x` | React frontend framework |\n| `react-dom` | `18.x` | React DOM renderer |\n| `typescript` | `5.x` | TypeScript compiler |\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `docs/docusaurus.config.ts` | create | Docusaurus configuration with site metadata, navbar, footer, plugins |\n| `docs/sidebars.ts` | create | Sidebar structure with categories for all documentation sections |\n| `docs/package.json` | create | npm dependencies and scripts for docs project |\n| `docs/tsconfig.json` | create | TypeScript configuration for strict mode |\n| `docs/src/pages/index.tsx` | create | Homepage with hero section and navigation buttons |\n| `docs/src/css/custom.css` | create | Custom styles overriding default theme |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/overview.md` | create | Architecture overview derived from `design.md` |\n| `docs/docs/architecture/sandbox.md` | create | Sandbox orchestration documentation |\n| `docs/docs/api/sdk-python/client.md` | create | Python SDK API reference |\n| `docs/docs/api/client-go/overview.md` | create | Go client-go API reference |\n| `docs/docs/deployment/kubernetes.md` | create | Kubernetes deployment guide |\n| `docs/docs/deployment/helm-chart.md` | create | Helm chart parameters documentation |\n| `docs/docs/getting-started/installation.md` | create | Installation prerequisites and commands |\n| `docs/docs/getting-started/first-sandbox.md` | create | First sandbox tutorial |\n| `docs/docs/changelog/index.md` | create | Changelog index page |\n| `.github/workflows/docs.yml` | create | GitHub Actions workflow for docs CI/CD |\n| `README.md` | modify | Add documentation site link, simplify content |\n| `Makefile` | modify | Add `docs` and `docs-start` targets |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- proposal.md — AR-042 detailed proposal and alternatives\n- project.md — AgentCube tech stack and conventions\n- design.md — Source for architecture documentation\n- deployment/design.md — Source for deployment guide\n- sandbox-orchestration/design.md — Source for sandbox documentation\n- sdk-python/ — Source for Python SDK API reference\n- client-go/ — Source for Go client API reference\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Docusaurus project initialized with TypeScript template\n- [ ] `docusaurus.config.ts` contains all required fields\n- [ ] Navbar items link to valid documentation routes\n- [ ] Sidebar categories and items resolve correctly\n- [ ] Architecture pages render with Mermaid diagrams\n- [ ] API reference pages include working code examples\n- [ ] Deployment guide documents Kubernetes and Helm\n- [ ] Getting started pages follow logical sequence\n- [ ] Changelog page lists releases correctly\n- [ ] Search integration works (Algolia or local)\n- [ ] i18n directories initialized for zh-Hans\n- [ ] GitHub Actions workflow triggers on docs changes\n- [ ] Homepage renders with hero and CTA buttons\n- [ ] Custom CSS applies branding styles\n- [ ] Makefile docs targets execute successfully\n- [ ] Local dev server starts on port 3000\n- [ ] Build output in `docs/build/` is valid static site"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-042/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-042/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775904089582,"end":1775904089610}}}}
